rvice.ts` returns `matchedUser` with nickname, but the repository/model layer do
esn\'t seem to pass it through correctly. Let me check the generated model.\n\nL
ooking at `matching_repository_impl.dart`:\n```dart\nif (response.data.isMatch =
= true) {\n  emit(MatchingMatchCreated({\n    \'match_id\': response.data.matchI
d,\n    \'conversation_id\': response.data.conversationId,\n    \'matched_user\'
: {\'user_id\': event.targetId},\n  }));\n}\n```\n\nThe `matched_user` only cont
ains `user_id`, not `nickname`. But the API response includes `matched_user` wit
h `nickname`. The bloc is not using the response data properly. This is a Major 
issue.\n\nAlso, `MatchingBloc._onSwipeActionSubmitted` should probably wait for 
the dialog to be dismissed before transitioning back, or preserve the cards when
