atar_url: c.avatar_url || undefined,\n}));\n```\n\nWhen `avatar_url` is null/und
efined, it\'s omitted from the response object (because `undefined` is not seria
lized in JSON). But the Dart model requires `avatar_url` to be present and non-n
ull. This would cause parsing to fail!\n\nWait, in the OpenAPI schema:\n```yaml\
nRecommendationCard:\n  type: object\n  required:\n    - user_id\n    - nickname
