API schema, the backend must always provide it (even if empty string). Or if it\
's truly optional, the OpenAPI schema should not mark it as required.\n\nLooking
at the PRD: "each card should contain: user_id, nickname, age, distance, bio, av
atar_url" - this suggests avatar_url should be present. But in practice, users m
ight not have avatars.\n\nThe OpenAPI schema marks `avatar_url` as required, but
