    type='think',
    think='Let me now also check if the `docs/product-specs/matching.md` exists 
and what\'s in it, since `docs/modules/INDEX.md` references it.\n\nAlso, I want 
to check if `matching.controller.ts` properly validates the `mode` parameter. It
accepts any string and passes it to the service. The service only checks for `na
tionwide` and `city`, defaulting to 50km for everything else. There\'s no valida
tion that mode is one of the allowed values. This is Minor.\n\nAlso, I want to v
erify if `MatchingBloc` properly handles the case where `recordAction` throws an
exception after `MatchingSwipeInProgress` was emitted. Looking at `_onSwipeActio
nSubmitted`:\n```dart\nemit(MatchingSwipeInProgress(...));\ntry {\n  final respo
nse = await _matchingRepository.recordAction(...);\n  // ...\n} on Exception cat
ch (e) {\n  emit(MatchingFailure(e.toString()));\n}\n```\n\nIf the API call fail
s, the state transitions from `MatchingSwipeInProgress` to `MatchingFailure`. Th
e UI would show a SnackBar (via listener) but the card was already removed from 
the local state. The user can\'t retry the swipe on the same card because it\'s 
gone. This is a UX issue but not blocking.\n\nActually, looking more carefully, 
in `_onSwipeActionSubmitted`:\n```dart\nfinal remainingCards = currentState.card
s.where((c) => c.userId != event.targetId).toList();\nemit(MatchingSwipeInProgre
ss(cards: remainingCards, ...));\n```\n\nSo the card is removed BEFORE the API c
all. If the API fails, the card is gone forever. This is a Major issue because n
etwork failures cause cards to disappear.\n\nSimilarly, in `HomePage._CardStackA
rea`, the card index is incremented in `_onAnimationStatusChanged` BEFORE callin
g `widget.onSwipe`. Actually:\n```dart\nwidget.onSwipe?.call(_currentIndex, dire
ction);\nsetState(() {\n  _currentIndex++;\n});\n```\n\nSo `onSwipe` is called w
ith the current index, then the index is incremented. In the BLoC, the card is r
emoved when `SwipeActionSubmitted` is processed. So if the API fails, the card i
s gone. This is definitely a Major issue.\n\nWait, but the animation completes, 
so the user sees the card fly away. If the API fails, they can\'t get it back. T
his is poor UX but the user can refresh. I\'ll mark it Major.\n\nNow let me also
think about whether there are any issues with `MatchListCubit`. It doesn\'t supp
ort pagination (loading more when scrolling). The `fetchMatches` method always r
eplaces the list, never appends. And there\'s no `loadMore` method. The state ha
s `hasMore` and `nextCursor` but they\'re never used for pagination. This is a M
ajor issue because the match list can\'t paginate.\n\nAlso, in `match_list_page.
dart`, when `hasMore` is true, it shows a `CircularProgressIndicator` at the bot
tom, but there\'s no logic to actually load more items when the user scrolls to 
it. The `onTap` is also a TODO. This is a functional gap. Major.\n\nLet me also 
check the `matching.md` module doc more carefully for the cache key issue. It sa
ys:\n```\nRedis 键：`recommendations:{user_id}`\n```\n\nBut the code uses `recom
